le\";s:18:\"2026/07/torero.jpg\";s:8:\"filesize\";i:473694;s:5:\"sizes\";a:2:{s:6:\"medium\";a:5:{s:4:\"file\";s:18:\"torero-278x300.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:278;s:6:\"height\";i:300;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";s:8:\"filesize\";i:20309;}s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:5:{s:4:\"file\";s:18:\"torero-150x150.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:150;s:6:\"height\";i:150;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";s:8:\"filesize\";i:6599;}}s:10:\"image_meta\";a:13:{s:8:\"aperture\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";s:1:\"0\";s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";s:1:\"0\";s:3:\"iso\";s:1:\"0\";s:13:\"shutter_speed\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";s:1:\"1\";s:8:\"keywords\";a:0:{}s:3:\"alt\";s:0:\"\";}}'),(1006,128,'sex','gelding'),(1007,128,'_sex','field_equine_sex'),(1008,128,'breed','Andalusian'),(1009,128,'_breed','field_equine_breed'),(1010,128,'height_cm',158),(1011,128,'_height_cm','field_equine_height'),(1012,128,'born_year',2000),(1013,128,'_born_year','field_equine_born_year'),(1014,128,'rescue_date',20210701),(1015,128,'_rescue_date','field_equine_rescue_date'),(1016,128,'favourite_food','Special Softened Hay'),(1017,128,'_favourite_food','field_equine_favourite_food'),(1018,128,'dislikes','Not being the centre of attention'),(1019,128,'_dislikes','field_equine_dislikes'),(1020,128,'quirk','Loves scratches!'),(1021,128,'_quirk','field_equine_quirk'),(1022,128,'personality','Gentle giant'),(1023,128,'_personality','field_equine_personality'),(1024,128,'rescue_picture',308),(1025,128,'_rescue_picture','field_equine_rescue_picture'),(1026,128,'rescue_story','This beautiful palomino was rescued by Spanish police from an abusive horse dealer (who is now serving a jail term for animal cruelty). Torero needed complex and major surgery to get back on his feet. \r\n\r\nMost horses at the rescue centre follow the same path: they\'re rescued, rehabilitated, and rehomed, so ARCH can focus on caring for the next animal in need. Torero can\'t follow that path. Because of his medical needs, he can’t be adopted — he\'ll live out his life at ARCH, and his care has to be funded for that time. That costs us around €350 a month, on top of everything else we need to fund.\r\n\r\nHow you can help:\r\n€ 13 → a few days of Torero\'s specialist soft-food diet\r\n€ 40 → roughly a week of his diet and supplements\r\n€ 90 → a quarter of his monthly care cost\r\n\r\nEvery donation, big or small, helps Torero\r\n'),(1027,128,'_rescue_story','field_equine_rescue_story'),(1029,310,'footnotes',''),(1030,310,'hero_photo',118),(1031,310,'_hero_photo','field_hero_photo'),(1032,310,'about_photo',241),(1033,310,'_about_photo','field_about_photo'),(1034,310,'hero_photo_link','https://overtakefan.s2-tastewp.com/equines/torero/'),(1035,310,'_hero_photo_link','field_hero_photo_link'),(1036,311,'footnotes',''),(1037,311,'hero_photo',118),(1038,311,'_hero_photo','field_hero_photo'),(1039,311,'about_photo',241),(1040,311,'_about_photo','field_about_photo'),(1041,311,'hero_photo_link','https://overtakefan.s2-tastewp.com/equines/torero/'),(1042,311,'_hero_photo_link','field_hero_photo_link'),(1047,313,'footnotes',''),(1049,123,'hero_sticker','Officially Utilidad Pública 🎉'),(1050,123,'_hero_sticker','field_hero_sticker'),(1051,123,'hero_lede','We\'re ARCH — a volunteer-powered rescue in Andalucía giving abandoned and abused equines a second chance at a good life. You\'ve been supporting us since 2009.'),(1052,123,'_hero_lede','field_hero_lede'),(1053,123,'hero_tag','Horse of the Month'),(1054,123,'_hero_tag','field_hero_tag'),(1055,123,'about_heading','Transforming Equine Lives since 2009.'),(1056,123,'_about_heading','field_about_heading'),(1057,123,'about_text_1','We\'re the Andalusian Rescue Centre for Horses — registered as Centro Andalusí de Rescate de Caballos, but known locally as ARCH. Our mission is to <strong>rescue equines who have been abused, neglected, or abandoned</strong> – animals who have no one else to fight for their well-being. Most of our rescues come through SEPRONA (the animal welfare arm of the Guardia Civil), and abandoned animals are also brought in through the local police. Inevitably some of the older animals, or those with special needs, stay with us for a long time but <strong>the Centre is not a retirement home or a sanctuary</strong>, and we try to find suitable homes for all our rescue animals.'),(1058,123,'_about_text_1','field_about_text_1'),(1059,123,'about_text_2','Rescue is only part of the story. Once animals arrive at the Rescue Centre we work with SEPRONA, local equine vets and with our animal rights lawyer, <strong>Aritz Toribio</strong>, to take owners to court. This is a <strong>costly, frustrating and long-drawn-out process.</strong> New animal cruelty legislation has been slow to filter through to judges and public prosecutors, but <strong>there have been some successful cases recently which give us hope</strong> that we may eventually win the fight for justice.'),(1060,123,'_about_text_2','field_about_text_2'),(1061,123,'contact_email','info@horserescuespain.org'),(1062,123,'_contact_email','field_contact_email'),(1063,123,'contact_address','Viña Borrego (behind Miralmonte), A404, Alhaurín el Grande, Málaga, Spain'),(1064,123,'_contact_address','field_contact_address'),(1065,123,'contact_hours','Mon–Sat, 9:00–11:00am by appointment. First Sunday of the month, 10am–2pm (except July & August).'),(1066,123,'_contact_hours','field_contact_hours'),(1067,123,'contact_visiting_info','Please wear closed shoes if you wish to groom or enter the paddocks. Visits are free of charge, but any donations are gratefully received!'),(1068,123,'_contact_visiting_info','field_contact_visiting_info'),(1069,123,'contact_sponsorship','Email sponsors@horserescuespain.org or use the form — just let us know which horse you\'d like to sponsor and we\'ll help you get set up.'),(1070,123,'_contact_sponsorship','field_contact_sponsorship'),(1071,313,'hero_photo',118),(1072,313,'_hero_photo','field_hero_photo'),(1073,313,'about_photo',241),(1074,313,'_about_photo','field_about_photo'),(1075,313,'hero_photo_link','https://overtakefan.s2-tastewp.com/equines/torero/'),(1076,313,'_hero_photo_link','field_hero_photo_link'),(1077,313,'hero_sticker','Officially Utilidad Pública 🎉'),(1078,313,'_hero_sticker','field_hero_sticker'),(1079,313,'hero_lede','We\'re ARCH — a volunteer-powered rescue in Andalucía giving abandoned and abused equines a second chance at a good life. You\'ve been supporting us since 2009.'),(1080,313,'_hero_lede','field_hero_lede'),(1081,313,'hero_tag','Horse of the Month'),(1082,313,'_hero_tag','field_hero_tag'),(1083,313,'about_heading','Transforming Equine Lives since 2009.'),(1084,313,'_about_heading','field_about_heading'),(1085,313,'about_text_1','We\'re the Andalusian Rescue Centre for Horses — registered as Centro Andalusí de Rescate de Caballos, but known locally as ARCH. Our mission is to <strong>rescue equines who have been abused, neglected, or abandoned</strong> – animals who have no one else to fight for their well-being. Most of our rescues come through SEPRONA (the animal welfare arm of the Guardia Civil), and abandoned animals are also brought in through the local police. Inevitably some of the older animals, or those with special needs, stay with us for a long time but <strong>the Centre is not a retirement home or a sanctuary</strong>, and we try to find suitable homes for all our rescue animals.'),(1086,313,'_about_text_1','field_about_text_1'),(1087,313,'about_text_2','Rescue is only part of the story. Once animals arrive at the Rescue Centre we work with SEPRONA, local equine vets and with our animal rights lawyer, <strong>Aritz Toribio</strong>, to take owners to court. This is a <strong>costly, frustrating and long-drawn-out process.</strong> New animal cruelty legislation has been slow to filter through to judges and public prosecutors, but <strong>there have been some successful cases recently which give us hope</strong> that we may eventually win the fight for justice.'),(1088,313,'_about_text_2','field_about_text_2'),(1089,313,'contact_email','info@horserescuespain.org'),(1090,313,'_contact_email','field_contact_email'),(1091,313,'contact_address','Viña Borrego (behind Miralmonte), A404, Alhaurín el Grande, Málaga, Spain'),(1092,313,'_contact_address','field_contact_address'),(1093,313,'contact_hours','Mon–Sat, 9:00–11:00am by appointment. First Sunday of the month, 10am–2pm (except July & August).'),(1094,313,'_contact_hours','field_contact_hours'),(1095,313,'contact_visiting_info','Please wear closed shoes if you wish to groom or enter the paddocks. Visits are free of charge, but any donations are gratefully received!'),(1096,313,'_contact_visiting_info','field_contact_visiting_info'),(1097,313,'contact_sponsorship','Email sponsors@horserescuespain.org or use the form — just let us know which horse you\'d like to sponsor and we\'ll help you get set up.'),(1098,313,'_contact_sponsorship','field_contact_sponsorship'),(1099,314,'footnotes',''),(1100,314,'hero_photo',118),(1101,314,'_hero_photo','field_hero_photo'),(1102,314,'about_photo',241),(1103,314,'_about_photo','field_about_photo'),(1104,314,'hero_photo_link','https://overtakefan.s2-tastewp.com/equines/torero/'),(1105,314,'_hero_photo_link','field_hero_photo_link'),(1106,314,'hero_sticker','Officially Utilidad Pública 🎉'),(1107,314,'_hero_sticker','field_hero_sticker'),(1108,314,'hero_lede','We\'re ARCH — a volunteer-powered rescue in Andalucía giving abandoned and abused equines a second chance at a good life. You\'ve been supporting us since 2009.'),(1109,314,'_hero_lede','field_hero_lede'),(1110,314,'hero_tag','Horse of the Month'),(1111,314,'_hero_tag','field_hero_tag'),(1112,314,'about_heading','Transforming Equine Lives since 2009.'),(1113,314,'_about_heading','field_about_heading'),(1114,314,'about_text_1','We\'re the Andalusian Rescue Centre for H