ainful and sometimes fatal condition affecting horses’ hooves. His feet had been left untrimmed for so long that they had curled up and forced him to walk on his heels. As far as we could tell, he hadn’t walked properly for years. It still took him a long while to get used to walking normally again. His feet had probably never been trimmed, so we had to give him pain relief to help him get through that until he got better.\r\n'),(1453,393,'_rescue_story','field_equine_rescue_story'),(1454,393,'cmplz_hide_cookiebanner',''),(1455,396,'_acf_changed',''),(1456,396,'footnotes',''),(1461,321,'wpforms_entries_count_previous_week','a:3:{i:0;i:4;i:1;i:4;i:2;i:0;}'),(1462,339,'wpforms_entries_count_previous_week','a:3:{i:0;i:1;i:1;i:1;i:2;i:0;}');
